main event: An unidentified flying object was reported in Minneapolis, Minnesota on December 6, 1966.
interesting points: The sighting was reported to the Air Force approximately one month after it occurred,The observation was made by a civilian,There is physical evidence noted but insufficient data for evaluation, A letter from a Lt. Colonel in the USAF was enclosed regarding the report, The detailed study was deemed difficult due to the late date of the report.
witness description: civilian observant of the unidentified flying object
